The paper discusses the security of permutation-only multimedia ciphers, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on multimedia data, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the attacks, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the cipher on images, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) or signal processing (cs.SI).
